Here's how to implement this in .NET MAUI Shell:

## 1. Custom "Cancel" Back Button

In your `EditProductPage.xaml`:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="YourApp.EditProductPage"
             Shell.BackButtonBehavior="{StaticResource CancelBackButton}">

    <ContentPage.Resources>
        <BackButtonBehavior x:Key="CancelBackButton"
                            TextOverride="Cancel"
                            Command="{Binding BackCommand}" />
    </ContentPage.Resources>

    <!-- your form here -->
</ContentPage>
```

## 2. Handle Back Navigation with Confirmation

In your code-behind or view model, intercept both the custom button and the hardware/gesture back:

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    public bool HasUnsavedChanges { get; set; }

    public ICommand BackCommand { get; }

    public EditProductPage()
    {
        BackCommand = new Command(async () => await TryGoBack());
        BindingContext = this;
        InitializeComponent();
    }

    // Intercept hardware/swipe back (Android back button, iOS swipe)
    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (HasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            // Fire-and-forget the async dialog; block the default nav
            _ = TryGoBack();
            return true; // cancel default back navigation
        }

        return false; // allow normal navigation
    }

    private async Task TryGoBack()
    {
        if (HasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (!leave)
                return; // user chose to stay
        }

        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    }
}
```

## Key points

- **`Shell.BackButtonBehavior`** — replaces the back arrow with a "Cancel" text button and binds it to your command.
- **`OnBackButtonPressed()`** — intercepts Android hardware back and iOS swipe-back; return `true` to cancel navigation.
- **`DisplayAlert`** — shows the confirmation dialog.
- **`Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..")`** — navigates back programmatically only after confirmation.

> **Caveat:** `OnBackButtonPressed` doesn't fire for the Shell toolbar back button on iOS/Windows — that's why `BackButtonBehavior.Command` is essential. Together they cover all back-navigation paths.
